        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Catch of the Moment: White Salmon'' (Sept. 20): At Petrossian, you can enjoy smoked white Alaskan king salmon with a variety of wonderful breads. But what about that oh-so-popular breakfast bread of sorts, the bagel?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Catch of the Moment: White Salmon'' (Sept. 20): At Petrossian, you can enjoy smoked white Alaskan king salmon with a variety of wonderful breads. But what about that oh-so-popular breakfast bread of sorts, the bagel?</p>
        <p>Well removed from the serenity of Alaska and the cosmopolitan charm of New York City, there's a small mom-and-pop bagel store here in Baltimore called Greg's Bagels that sells a delicious smoked white Alaskan king salmon. Greg Novik, the shop's owner, has aptly named this menu selection White Alaskan King Triple Smoke. Its delicacy and smooth smoke is as unique as the salmon's ivory color; the bagel and lox combination has never tasted better.</p>
        <p>MIKE SCARCELLA  Baltimore</p>
      </block>
